  // SAMPLE
  section
    legend.mdc-typography--display1 Grids

    mdc-grid

      mdc-grid-cell(span="12")
        p.
          This component is a wrapper around MDC Layout Grid which is a css only component.
          Read more about grids at #[a(href="https://material.io/components/web/catalog/layout-grids/" target="_blank" data-analytics-category="external" data-analytics-action="mdc-grids") Material components documentation]

        // LINKS
        hr
        section
          a(href="https://material.io/components/web/catalog/layout-grids/" target="_blank" data-analytics-category="external" data-analytics-action="mdc-grids") Material components documentation
        section
          a(href="https://material.io/guidelines/layout/responsive-ui.html#responsive-ui-grid" target="_blank" data-analytics-category="external" data-analytics-action="mdg-grids") Material design guidelines
        hr


        // COPY PASTE DESCRIPTION
        section
          legend.mdc-typography--headline The layout grid
          p.mdc-typography--caption (copy from Material documentation)
          p.
            A grid is a container that consists of a group of cells. 
            Grid can define its own max-width or designate its columns to be a 
            certain width. Cells get positioned in sequence according to a 
            predefined number of columns.
          p.
            The grid has 12 columns in desktop mode (&gt;= 840px), 8 columns in tablet mode (&gt;= 480px), 
            and 4 columns in phone mode (&lt; 480px). Cells specify how many columns to span (the default is 4). 
            Cells are placed side by side until there is no more room, then the next cell is placed at 
            the beginning of the next row.
          p.
            Margins (the space between the edge of the grid and the edge of the first cell) and 
            gutters (the space between edges of adjacent cells) can be customized on different devices respectively 
            based on design needs. The columns are evenly distributed within the container width, minus the width 
            of all margins and gutters. Layout grids set default margins and gutters to 24px on desktop, 16px on 
            tablet and phone, according to the Material Design spec.
          p.
            The grid and cells are not styled in any way, serving only for alignment and positioning of elements.

        // BASIC
        section
          legend.mdc-typography--headline Grid component
          p This is a #[span.mark-text basic] layout used with material components:
          pre
            code-prism.
              <div class="mdc-layout-grid">
                <div class="mdc-layout-grid__inner">
                  <div class="mdc-layout-grid__cell"></div>
                  <div class="mdc-layout-grid__cell"></div>
                  <div class="mdc-layout-grid__cell"></div>
                </div>
              </div>

          p Equal part with bridge component:
          pre
            code-prism.
              <mdc-grid>
                <mdc-grid-cell></mdc-grid-cell>
                <mdc-grid-cell></mdc-grid-cell>
                <mdc-grid-cell></mdc-grid-cell>
              </mdc-grid>

          // FIXED
          legend.mdc-typography--headline Fixed column width grid
          p.
            Set #[span.mark-text fixed-width] attribute to #[span.mark-text true] to add 
            #[span.mark-text class mdc-layout-grid--fixed-column-width] to #[span.mark-text mdc-layout-grid]:
          pre
            code-prism.
              <mdc-grid fixed-width="true">
                <mdc-grid-cell></mdc-grid-cell>
                <mdc-grid-cell></mdc-grid-cell>
                <mdc-grid-cell></mdc-grid-cell>
              </mdc-grid>
          
          // COLUMN SPANS
          legend.mdc-typography--headline Column spans
          p.
            To span columns set attributes #[span.mark-text span], #[span.mark-text span-desktop],
            #[span.mark-text span-tablet] and/or #[span.mark-text span-phone] to a numeric
            value (1-12):
          pre
            code-prism.
              <mdc-grid>
                <mdc-grid-cell span="2"></mdc-grid-cell>
                <mdc-grid-cell span="4"></mdc-grid-cell>
                <mdc-grid-cell span="6" span-tablet="8"></mdc-grid-cell>
              </mdc-grid>
          
          // REORDERING
          legend.mdc-typography--headline Reordering
          p.
            Reorder columns by setting attribute #[span.mark-text order] to a numeric
            value (1-12):
          pre
            code-prism.
              <mdc-grid>
                <mdc-grid-cell order="3"></mdc-grid-cell>
                <mdc-grid-cell order="1"></mdc-grid-cell>
                <mdc-grid-cell order="2"></mdc-grid-cell>
              </mdc-grid>

          // ALIGNMENT
          legend.mdc-typography--headline Alignment
          p.
            Align column content by setting attribute #[span.mark-text align] to a string
            value ("top", "middle", "bottom"):
          pre
            code-prism.
              <mdc-grid>
                <mdc-grid-cell align="top"></mdc-grid-cell>
                <mdc-grid-cell align="middle"></mdc-grid-cell>
                <mdc-grid-cell align="bottom"></mdc-grid-cell>
              </mdc-grid>

          // NESTED GRID
          legend.mdc-typography--headline Nested grid
          p.
            When your contents need extra structure that cannot be supported by single layout grid, 
            you can nest layout grid within each other. To nest layout grid, add a new #[span.mark-text mdc-layout-grid-inner] element to wrap around nested cells.
          p.mdc-typography--caption.
            (Material guideline do not recommend have a deeply nested grid since it might means a over complicated UX.)
          pre
            code-prism.
              <mdc-grid>
                <mdc-grid-cell>
                  <mdc-grid-inner>
                    <mdc-grid-cell></mdc-grid-cell>
                    <mdc-grid-cell></mdc-grid-cell>
                    <mdc-grid-cell></mdc-grid-cell>
                  </mdc-grid-inner>
                </mdc-grid-cell>
                <mdc-grid-cell></mdc-grid-cell>
                <mdc-grid-cell></mdc-grid-cell>
              </mdc-grid>
